*Lived:* 1711-1776

*Nationality:* Scottish 

*Profession:* Philosopher *fawn Actually, not really; mostly public servant and librarian at first and later historian and just occasionally philosopher.  He would have liked to be a full-time philosopher but there weren't many jobs for philosophers in those days and he couldn't get one. Jason*

*Main influence:* John Locke and Empiricism 

*Most important work:* A Treatise of Human Nature (1739–1740)